sec.p:
The practical implementation of the MHD-controlled inlets leads to some critical issues that remain to be verified, such as the position and length of the MHD interaction region, the distribution of the magnetic flux density in the interactive region, etc. As discussed in Lindsey et al. [13] and Van Wie and Nedungadi [21], and especially, the arguments presented in some details in Shenider et al. [22], two criteria can be allocated for the parameters, namely,


MHD interaction region should be placed as far upstream as possible;

MHD interaction region should be close to the magnetic coil centre-line.
